**Findings**
- Focus 4: The `DEVLOOP_NUMBERS` contract is not actually stable across ACs. `emit_numbers()` defines one shape for AC-013/013b (`ac/n/samples/p50_ms/p99_ms/recall_at_10/cache/embedder`), but AC-019 bypasses it and emits a different schema with no `samples`, `p50_ms`, `p99_ms`, or `recall_at_10`. The doc then says PR-7 parses `p50_ms`, `p99_ms`, and `recall_at_10` as the stable contract, which AC-019 cannot satisfy. Downstream either has to special-case AC-019 or it will misparse/skip it. Action: either normalize AC-019 onto the same keyed schema, or explicitly version/split the record types and document that. Refs: [perf_gates_devloop.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates_devloop.rs#L164), [perf_gates_devloop.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates_devloop.rs#L427), [perf-gates.md](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/dev/design/perf-gates.md#L113).
- Focus 3: The locked “real embedder requires warm cache” rule is documented but not enforced. `DEVLOOP_REAL_EMBEDDER=1` switches to `with_real_embedder()` unconditionally, and `setup()` never checks `report.embed_cache_hit`/`embedded_live` before running the suite. On a cold cache, this still does live BGE ingest for ~1000 docs and violates the stated opt-in contract. Action: after ingest, skip or fail early when `embedder == "real"` and the cache was not warm. Refs: [perf_gates_devloop.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates_devloop.rs#L96), [perf_gates_devloop.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates_devloop.rs#L242), [corpus_harness.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_harness.rs#L338), [perf-gates.md](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/dev/design/perf-gates.md#L79).
- Focus 2: The implementation does use the production `Engine::search` read path, but the comments about the real path are materially wrong. The harness cache wraps every `embed()` call, not just doc-body ingest, and AC-013/AC-019 do a warmup/baseline `search()` pass before measurement. That primes the held-out query texts too, so the measured `embedder=real` pass is not “live candle inference” for queries as claimed. Action: either exclude query texts from caching for measured real runs, or correct the code/doc comments so the numbers are not misinterpreted as end-to-end query-embed latency. Refs: [perf_gates_devloop.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates_devloop.rs#L42), [perf_gates_devloop.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates_devloop.rs#L268), [perf_gates_devloop.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates_devloop.rs#L376), [corpus_harness.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_harness.rs#L624).

**Other focus points**
- Focus 1: no new blocker. The two named regressions are wired to fail via the structural asserts in [perf_gates_devloop.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates_devloop.rs#L249) and the catastrophic ceiling in [perf_gates_devloop.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates_devloop.rs#L217).
- Focus 5: no bypass found. Writes go through the public harness/engine path and reads go through `Engine::search`; the raw SQLite connection is read-only GT only. Refs: [corpus_harness.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_harness.rs#L327), [perf_gates_devloop.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates_devloop.rs#L301), [lib.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs#L1819).
- Focus 6: no mismatch found. Synthetic GT reconstruction is valid because `VaryingEmbedder`’s vector generation depends only on `dim + text`; identity changes only affect cache keys. Refs: [perf_gates_devloop.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates_devloop.rs#L114), [corpus_subset.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_subset.rs#L304), [corpus_harness.rs](/home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_harness.rs#L443).

